		<h1>Help</h1>

		<h2 id="help_how_to">How to..</h2>
		<h3>How do I email my itinerary?</h3>
		<p>Select 'Send' from the main menu then select 'Email' and enter the required email
			address. For multi recipients you will be prompted if you want to send another email.</p>
		<h3>How do I print my itinerary?</h3>
		<p>Select 'Print' from the main menu, the itinerary will display in a new window ready
			for printing to the Windows selected printer. After printing, clicking 'Close' will
			close the active browser.</p>
		<h3>How do I view my Invoices?</h3>
		<p>Enter the Traveller surname and Booking reference then select Invoice Summary from
			the drop down menu. Alternatively enter the Invoice number or Ticket number in the
			last search field on screen. Description is currently collapsed. Click to expand.</p>
		<h3>There are 3 invoices for my next trip. How do I select a specific invoice?</h3>
		<p>My Travel Plans displays a list of all Invoices that were issued via American Express
			relating to that trip. Select the required invoice and click 'View/Download'. The
			Invoice is a PDF copy.</p>
		<h3>How do I re-print my Invoice?</h3>
		<p>Once you have selected the Invoice required, Select 'Print' from the main menu.
			The Invoice will display in a new window ready for printing to the Windows selected
			printer. After printing, click 'Close' and you will exit the active browser and
			be returned to the site.</p>
		<h3>How do I save my Invoice locally?</h3>
		<p>After you have clicked 'View/Download' on the required Invoice, it will open in
			another window. Simply click 'File'  'Save As'. We suggest you re-name the file
			from the reservation number to something more relevant to you so that you can locate
			it again when required.</p>
		<h3>How do I print my E-ticket Receipt?</h3>
		<p>Using the Internet Print functionality, select 'File'  'Print' from the Internet
			Main Menu bar above My Travel Plans. After printing, click 'Back' on the internet
			menu and you will be returned to the Main site. Do not click 'Close' or '(X)' or
			you will exit the site.</p>

		<h2 id="help_general">Help: General</h2>
		<h3>Why isn't my reservation displaying?</h3>
		<p>Please ensure you are using a valid six character reservation number. If this reference
			contains a &quot;O&quot; it may be either a letter or a number. The spelling of
			the Traveller's last name must be the identical to the travel reservation created.
			Please note:This site is not case sensitive.</p>
		<h3>Can I display my booking without my reservation number?</h3>
		<p>To ensure security of your data a second reference is always required in addition
			to the traveller's last name. If you do not have the Reservation number/Booking
			Reference, you will require an Invoice or Ticket Number to enter the site and can
			then access the Itinerary from the Main Menu.</p>
		<h3>Who can view my reservation on My Travel Plans?</h3>
		<p>Your travel information is secure and can only be viewed by those who you have provided
			your unique Booking Reference, Invoice Number or Ticket Number to. This may include
			your Travel arranger if they have access to this information.</p>
		<h3>How long is my reservation available on My Travel Plans?</h3>
		<p>Your Itinerary will remain accessible in My Travel Plans for as long as it is live
			in the travel reservation system. If your itinerary has a generated: &quot;time/date&quot;
			remark at the top indicating when it was last stored on the site, then these historical
			itineraries will remain in the system for 3 months after the last flight or land
			sector. This function is only available for some customers.</p>
		<h3>What else can I view on My Travel Plans?</h3>
		<p>All e-invoices issued for your reservation are available on My Travel Plans. All
			E-Tickets issued will also be available on My Travel Plans.</p>
		<h3>What browser does My Travel Plans support?</h3>
		<p>The latest version of all major browsers is supported.</p>
		<h3>Who do I contact if I have a problem with the My Travel Plans site in general?</h3>
		<p>Please check if your question is covered in this Help Site before contacting your
			local American Express Support team.</p>
		<h3>Has anything else changed with Itineraries and Invoices?</h3>
		<p>Online itineraries generated from booking tools have also been updated to include
			a link to My Travel Plans so that all Important Traveller Information from American
			Express can be accessed via the My Travel Plans itinerary. A new Invoice search
			function has also been added to the Home page. Simply enter the Traveller surname
			and Booking Reference, then select the Invoice Summary Page from the drop down menu.</p>

		<h2 id="help_itineraries">Help: Itineraries</h2>
		<h3>Can I make changes to my itinerary on My Travel Plans?</h3>
		<p>Changes cannot be completed on My Travel Plans. All changes must be made via AXO,
			your Travel consultant or the Interactive Support team.</p>
		<h3>When will the updated itinerary be available on My Travel Plans?</h3>
		<p>The updated itinerary will be reflected as soon as your travel consultant or booking
			tool has generated the changes through to this site. This site now stores Itineraries
			for historical purposes so if changes are made to your booking please always check
			the &quot;generated at time/date&quot; indicator to ensure the most recent itinerary
			is displayed. Please note: Some customers do not have access to historical itineraries
			and will only be able to view itineraries while they remain live in the reservation
			system. Description is currently collapsed. Click to expand.</p>
		<h3>How do I email my itinerary?</h3>
		<p>Select 'Send' from the main menu then select 'Email' and enter the required email
			address. For multiple recipients you will be prompted if you want to send another
			email.</p>
		<h3>How do I print my itinerary?</h3>
		<p>Select 'Print' from the main menu, the itinerary will display in a new window ready
			for printing to the Windows selected printer. After printing, clicking 'Close' will
			close the active browser.</p>

		<h2 id="help_invoices">Help: Invoices</h2>
		<h3>How do I view my Invoices?</h3>
		<p>Enter the Traveller surname and Booking reference then select Invoice Summary from
			the drop down menu. Alternatively enter the individual Invoice number or Ticket
			number in the last search field on screen.</p>
		<h3>Why is my Invoice not showing on My Travel Plans?</h3>
		<p>Your invoice may not have been issued as yet or may be older than 3 months. You
			may also be using an incorrect reference number. Please contact your travel consultant
			for further information</p>
		<h3>There are 3 invoices for my next trip. How do I select a specific invoice?</h3>
		<p>My Travel Plans displays a list of all Invoices that were issued via American Express
			relating to that trip. Select the required invoice and click 'View/Download'. The
			Invoice is a PDF copy.</p>
		<h3>How do I re-print my Invoice?</h3>
		<p>Once you have selected the Invoice required, Select 'Print' from the main menu.
			The Invoice will display in a new window ready for printing to the Windows selected
			printer. After printing, click 'Close' and you will exit the active browser and
			be returned to the site.</p>
		<h3>Can I store or save my Invoice locally?</h3>
		<p>After you have clicked 'View/Download' on the required Invoice, it will open in
			another window. Simply click 'File, Save As'. We suggest you re-name the file from
			the reservation number to something more relevant to you so that you can locate
			it again when required.</p>
		<h3>How long will my Invoice be available?</h3>
		<p>Your invoice will remain viewable for 6 months from date of issue.</p>
		<h3>Can I email my Invoice?</h3>
		<p>This site does not support the emailing of Invoices however this function is currently
			under review by American Express Compliance.</p>

		<h2 id="help_eticket">Help: eTicket Receipts</h2>
		<h3>Why isn't my full credit card number shown on my E-Ticket Receipt?</h3>
		<p>To protect your credit card from possible fraudulent use, your credit card number
			will only show the last four digits or may be blocked completely.</p>
		<h3>How do I print my E-ticket Receipt?</h3>
		<p>Using the Internet Print functionality, select 'File,Print' from the Internet Main
			Menu bar above My Travel Plans. After printing, click 'Back' on the internet menu
			and you will be returned to the Main site. Do not click 'Close' or '(X)' or you
			will exit the site.</p>

		<h2 id="help_dtc">Help: Download to Calendar</h2>
		<h3>Who do I contact if I have a problem with the PDA download?</h3>
		<p>Electronic calendar software can be different for every user so this functionality
			may not always work as designed. Should your own technical team be unable to assist
			you, please contact your American Express Support team and advise which electronic
			calendar functionality and version you are operating on i.e. Lotus Notes V6, Outlook
			etc</p>
		<h3>Am I able to download to calendar?</h3>
		<p>This function is not available to all customers and is currently under review for
			future development on our new platform. A &quot;download to calendar&quot; link
			will show to the right of your itinerary if this function is available. Description
			is currently collapsed. Click to expand.</p>

